events.name: Appalachian State Mountaineers at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Jalen Hurd recovered quarterback Joshua Dobbs' overtime fumble in the end zone, and No. 9 Tennessee overcame a 10-point halftime deficit to escape with a 20-13 victory over Appalachian State.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 9 Tennessee edges Appalachian State 20-13 in OT

video.headline: No. 9 Tennessee survives scare from Appalachian State

headlines.description: Lamar Jackson accounted for a school-record eight touchdowns and 405 offensive yards by halftime to help No. 19 Louisville dismantle Charlotte 70-14 on Thursday night in the season opener for bot

video.headline: Louisville routs Charlotte behind Jackson's eight first-half TDs

headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson has hand in L'ville-record 8 TDs in rout

events.name: Presbyterian College Blue Hose at Central Michigan Chippewas

headlines.description: Jahray Hayes ran for three touchdowns and Central Michigan rolled over Presbyterian 49-3 in the season opener for both teams on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayes scores 3 TDs, Central Michigan routs Presbyterian 49-3

video.headline: Willis won't be denied to break game open for CMU

events.name: Tulane Green Wave at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Kendall Hinton ran for a short early touchdown and Wake Forest overcame some offensive struggles and held on for a season-opening 7-3 victory over Tulane on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Despite offensive woes, Wake Forest holds off Tulane 7-3

video.headline: Hinton's 1-yard TD proves the difference for Wake Forest

events.name: UT Martin Skyhawks at Cincinnati Bearcats

headlines.description: Hayden Moore threw for 260 yards and two touchdowns, Mike Boone ran for a score and Cincinnati beat UT Martin 28-7 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincinnati scores 22 points in 2nd half, tops UT Martin 28-7

video.headline: Holcombe ices the game for Cincinnati with pick-six

events.name: Maine Black Bears at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Bobby Puyol hit a 37-yard field goal with 11 seconds left and UConn avoided a season-opening upset with a 24-21 win over Maine from the Football Championship Subdivision on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Puyol's kick gives UConn a 24-21 win over Maine

video.headline: UConn escapes on Puyol's late FG

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Florida Intl Golden Panthers

headlines.description: Richard Lagow passed for one score and ran for another in the fourth quarter, and Indiana returned two interceptions for touchdowns in its season-opening 34-13 win over Florida International on T
headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana gets 3 late TDs, gets past FIU 34-13 in opener

video.headline: Indiana ices the game with second pick-six

events.name: William & Mary Tribe at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Jaylen Samuels and Matt Dayes combined to score five touchdowns to help North Carolina State beat William & Mary 48-14 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Finley starts at QB, NC State beats William & Mary 48-14

video.headline: Samuels' third TD of the game leads rout for NC State

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Elliott Fry kicked a career-long 55-yard field goal with 35 seconds left, and the South Carolina Gamecocks rallied from a 10-point halftime deficit to beat Vanderbilt 13-10 Thursday night in Will
headlines.shortLinkText: South Carolina rallies, beats Vanderbilt 13-10 in SEC opener

video.headline: Fry puts South Carolina ahead with last-minute 55-yard FG

events.name: Southern Utah Thunderbirds at Utah Utes

headlines.description: Troy Williams threw for 272 yards and two touchdowns as Utah opened the season with a 24-0 victory over Southern Utah on Thursday evening.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams, defense leads Utah to 24-0 win over Southern Utah

video.headline: Patrick goes 57 yards on TD catch to finish off Utah's win

events.name: Weber State Wildcats at Utah State Aggies

headlines.description: Devante Mays rushed for 208 yards and scored three touchdowns in a span of 15 minutes to power Utah State to a 45-6 victory over Weber State in the season-opener for both schools Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mays runs for 3 TDs, Utah State runs over Weber State, 45-6

events.name: Rice Owls at Western Kentucky Hilltoppers

headlines.description: Mike White threw for 517 yards and three touchdowns in his debut as starting quarterback as Western Kentucky opened the season and Conference USA play with a 46-14 drubbing of Rice.
headlines.shortLinkText: White throws for 517 yards as W. Kentucky beats Rice 46-14

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: Rodney Smith rushed for 125 yards and two touchdowns and Minnesota overcame three ejections for targeting to beat Oregon State 30-23 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Minnesota hangs on for 30-23 victory over Oregon State

events.name: South Dakota Coyotes at New Mexico Lobos

headlines.description: Teriyon Gipson scored on the first play from scrimmage and New Mexico continued to pile up yards and points against South Dakota in a 48-21 victory on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: New Mexico cruises past South Dakota 48-21

events.name: Jackson State Tigers at UNLV Rebels

headlines.description: Johnny Stanton was 10 of 12 for 217 yards and he threw three touchdown passes to Devonte Boyd to help UNLV beat FCS-level Jackson State 63-13 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boyd scores 3 TDs, UNLV beats FCS-level Jackson State 63-13
